This error message usually occurs when you are trying to execute a SQL Server command using the ExecuteNonQuery method without initializing the Transaction property of the command. In other words, the connection assigned to the command is already in the middle of a pending transaction, but the code does not specify any transaction to be used for the command.

To resolve this issue, you need to initialize the Transaction property of the SqlCommand object with a valid SqlTransaction object before calling the ExecuteNonQuery() method. This can be done using the BeginTransaction method of the SqlConnection object. Here is an example code snippet that demonstrates how to use a transaction with SqlCommand:

```csharp
using (SqlConnection connection = new SqlConnection(connectionString))
{
    connection.Open();

    SqlTransaction transaction = connection.BeginTransaction();

    try
    {
        SqlCommand command = connection.CreateCommand();
        command.Transaction = transaction;

        // set up your SQL command here
        command.CommandText = "INSERT INTO MyTable (Column1, Column2) VALUES (@value1, @value2)";
        command.Parameters.AddWithValue("@value1", value1);
        command.Parameters.AddWithValue("@value2", value2);

        int rowsAffected = command.ExecuteNonQuery();

        // commit the transaction
        transaction.Commit();
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        // rollback the transaction on error
        transaction.Rollback();

        // log or re-throw the exception
    }
}
```

In this example, we create a SqlConnection object and open it. Then we create a SqlTransaction object by calling the BeginTransaction method of the connection, which puts the connection into an active transaction mode. We then create a SqlCommand object and assign the transaction to its Transaction property. Finally, we execute the SQL command using the ExecuteNonQuery method and commit the transaction if the command succeeds, or rollback the transaction if we encounter an error.

这个错误通常会出现在使用ExecuteNonQuery方法执行SQL Server命令时，没有初始化命令的Transaction属性。换句话说，指定给命令的连接已经处于挂起的事务中，但是代码并没有指定任何事务来执行这个命令。

为了解决这个问题，在调用ExecuteNonQuery方法之前，你需要使用一个有效的SqlTransaction对象初始化SqlCommand对象的Transaction属性。这可以使用SqlConnection对象的BeginTransaction方法来完成。以下是一个示例代码片段，演示了如何在SqlCommand中使用事务：

```csharp
using (SqlConnection connection = new SqlConnection(connectionString))
{
    connection.Open();

    SqlTransaction transaction = connection.BeginTransaction();

    try
    {
        SqlCommand command = connection.CreateCommand();
        command.Transaction = transaction;

        // 设置你的SQL命令
        command.CommandText = "INSERT INTO MyTable (Column1, Column2) VALUES (@value1, @value2)";
        command.Parameters.AddWithValue("@value1", value1);
        command.Parameters.AddWithValue("@value2", value2);

        int rowsAffected = command.ExecuteNonQuery();

        // 提交事务
        transaction.Commit();
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        // 事务回滚
        transaction.Rollback();

        // 记录或抛出异常
    }
}
```

在这个例子中，我们创建了一个SqlConnection对象并打开它。然后，我们通过调用连接的BeginTransaction方法来创建一个SqlTransaction对象，将连接置于活动事务模式。接下来，我们创建了一个SqlCommand对象并将事务分配给它的Transaction属性。最后，我们使用ExecuteNonQuery方法执行SQL命令，并在命令成功后提交事务，或者在遇到错误时回滚事务。
